</div>
<div id="col2">
    <h3>Eligibility</h3>
<ul><li>Full-time faculty and staff of member universities</li>
<li>Full-time employees of R&amp;E network members, industry members and SEGP institutions</li>
<li>Full-time employees of state governments or of the US Federal government</li></ul>

<p>Employers are required to commit to re-employment at the conclusion of a Fellow's tenure at Internet2.</p>

<h3>Funding</h3>
<p>The Internet2 Fellows program is intended to be compensation-neutral for participants. Financial support is available from Internet2; however, funds for this purpose are limited and prospective Fellows are encouraged to explore other sources of support, such as the NSF Grant Opportunities for Academic Liaison with Industry (GOALI) program. (In the GOALI context, Internet2 has the role of "industry.")</p>

<p>Federal employees may become Internet2 Fellows through the provisions of the Intergovernmental Personnel Act (IPA).  (Although Internet2 qualifies for participation under the general rules of the IPA, federal agencies differ in their interpretation of the Act, so prospective Fellows should check with their agency's legal counsel.)</p>

<p>Fellows are not required to relocate, and Internet2 will not pay for relocation. Travel and other reimbursable expenses incurred during a Fellow's tenure will be paid by Internet2.</p>

<h3>Process</h3>
<p>Prospective Presidential Fellows should contact the office of the Internet2 CEO directly.  All others interested in a Fellow position should initially contact the intended Internet2 staff collaborator to discuss the collaboration, including the anticipated outcomes and community benefits, and funding considerations. If and when the applicant and the agree in general on the description of a project of mutual interest, the applicant must <strong><a href="&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#099;&#116;&#111;&#064;&#105;&#110;&#116;&#101;&#114;&#110;&#101;&#116;&#050;&#046;&#101;&#100;&#117;?&#115;&#117;&#098;&#106;&#101;&#099;&#116;=&#070;&#101;&#108;&#108;&#111;&#119;&#115;&#032;&#080;&#114;&#111;&#103;&#114;&#097;&#109;&#032;&#073;&#110;&#113;&#117;&#105;&#114;&#121;">submit a detailed proposal</a></strong>, which must include:</p>

<ul>
<li>A description of the work to be carried out, including deliverables (for example, beta software, journal article or conference paper, webinar series)</li>
<li>The anticipated benefits to Internet2, to the Fellow's home institution, and to the R&amp;E community</li>
<li>The proposed duration of the relationship and fraction of time, if less than full-time</li>
<li>Funding details, including sources of external support (if applicable)</li>
<li>An official letter from the applicant's employer giving permission for the applicant to participate in the Internet2 Fellows Program and a commitment to re-employment.</li>
</ul>  

<p>The applicant's proposal, together with a supporting document from the Internet2 collaborator, will be reviewed internally by Internet2 staff and by a representative or subcommittee of the Program Advisory Group for the Internet2 Division of the proposed collaborator.</p>

<p>The existence and contents of proposals are held in confidence and divulged only to those directly involved in the review process.</p>

<p>Proposals may be submitted at any time.</p>

</div>
